 "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t",
 StyleBox["Figure Siemens star with line marker:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " I have included a dark rectangular region at left\n\nThis type of feature \
will make the Fourier filtering affects more obvious and help me to see if \
things are working correctly."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.760650838621871*^9, 3.760650887671479*^9}, {
   3.760651276765469*^9, 3.760651661859634*^9}, {3.76065171408908*^9, 
   3.760651863463242*^9}, {3.7606526647727137`*^9, 3.760652678754582*^9}, {
   3.760653565490666*^9, 3.760653566800193*^9}, {3.760654426413691*^9, 
   3.760654564633397*^9}, 3.760654652980967*^9, {3.760655529537733*^9, 
   3.760655556132839*^9}, {3.760736136762182*^9, 
   3.760736137453895*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4fc472fe-1f01-4464-b713-\
234e839819a6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 StyleBox["2.2.1 Construct and investigate the effects of a low pass filter \
on images\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\tThis will essentially produce the same results as the previous section \
but the idea is to only pass a small radius of the Fourier spectra centered \
at the DC spatial frequency location. \n\tTherefore, the Fourier filter \
should be either a disc of radius ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["f", "r"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d71f3a82-ae32-4e75-b254-1a64ab0c4ea9"],
 " or a super Gaussian function similar to the last section."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7606384664822483`*^9, 3.760638476973008*^9}, {
   3.760642843021214*^9, 3.7606428654108677`*^9}, {3.7606429319635153`*^9, 
   3.760642946184031*^9}, {3.760643099797296*^9, 3.760643188108944*^9}, {
   3.760643226753291*^9, 3.760643238862667*^9}, {3.760643343234527*^9, 
   3.760643361069058*^9}, {3.76064349367705*^9, 3.760643534433504*^9}, {
   3.760643608463779*^9, 3.760643634434759*^9}, {3.760643916989945*^9, 
   3.76064407491961*^9}, {3.760644140809655*^9, 3.760644205629078*^9}, 
   3.760644359185997*^9, {3.760644449894362*^9, 3.760644460348439*^9}, {
   3.760645562995447*^9, 3.760645594382709*^9}, {3.7606508200347548`*^9, 
   3.760650820526434*^9}, {3.760652906042602*^9, 3.7606529084093657`*^9}, {
   3.760653281226163*^9, 3.760653299505703*^9}, {3.760653580114511*^9, 
   3.7606536562433367`*^9}, {3.760653703201256*^9, 
   3.760653723856781*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7ddff68b-9190-456a-8bb7-\
bb7915bc967e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Deliverable: ",
  FontSize->13,
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["Vary the filter size and include a plot like the one from the last \
section to show that your spatial filter works.\n\n1) Discuss what effects \
you see in the Siemens star image\n2) How could you use this particular \
object to determine the resolution of your imaging system and quantify the \
effects of the Fourier filtering you have applied? ",
  FontSize->13]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.760653317870872*^9, 3.760653379482809*^9}, {
  3.76065343862327*^9, 3.760653498432395*^9}, {3.760654097147524*^9, 
  3.76065411177414*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"868df18b-af71-4453-a1d5-dcf794f7af01"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 StyleBox["2.2.2 Construct and investigate the effects of a high pass filter \
on images\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\tA high pass filter can be constructed as the \[OpenCurlyQuote]inverse\
\[CloseCurlyQuote] of a low pass filter i.e., it lets light through only in \
the location where the low pass filter blocks light."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7606384664822483`*^9, 3.760638476973008*^9}, {
   3.760642843021214*^9, 3.7606428654108677`*^9}, {3.7606429319635153`*^9, 
   3.760642946184031*^9}, {3.760643099797296*^9, 3.760643188108944*^9}, {
   3.760643226753291*^9, 3.760643238862667*^9}, {3.760643343234527*^9, 
   3.760643361069058*^9}, {3.76064349367705*^9, 3.760643534433504*^9}, {
   3.760643608463779*^9, 3.760643634434759*^9}, {3.760643916989945*^9, 
   3.76064407491961*^9}, {3.760644140809655*^9, 3.760644205629078*^9}, 
   3.760644359185997*^9, {3.760644449894362*^9, 3.760644460348439*^9}, {
   3.760645562995447*^9, 3.760645594382709*^9}, {3.7606508200347548`*^9, 
   3.760650820526434*^9}, {3.760652906042602*^9, 3.7606529084093657`*^9}, {
   3.760653281226163*^9, 3.760653329256733*^9}, {3.76065347713719*^9, 
   3.760653478650423*^9}, {3.7606541214186296`*^9, 
   3.7606541477422867`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"216cd0fe-7865-4404-8e96-\
b8b938323cc9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Deliverable: ",
  FontSize->13,
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["Vary the filter size and include a plot like the one from the last \
section to show that your spatial filter works.\n\n1) Discuss what effects \
you see in the Siemens star image\n2) What purpose can this filter serve in \
image processing?",
  FontSize->13]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.760653317870872*^9, 3.760653379482809*^9}, {
  3.76065343862327*^9, 3.760653498432395*^9}, {3.760654097147524*^9, 
  3.76065411177414*^9}, {3.7606541679107637`*^9, 3.7606541737865868`*^9}, {
  3.7606542990355253`*^9, 3.76065430770083*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"ddf3345b-eb21-44b5-8791-5717f9ac8bbc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 StyleBox["2.2.3 Construct and investigate the effects of a band-pass filter \
on images\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\tA band-pass filter can be constructed as the difference between two low \
pass filters. That is, the band-pass filter is a ring in Fourier space. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7606384664822483`*^9, 3.760638476973008*^9}, {
   3.760642843021214*^9, 3.7606428654108677`*^9}, {3.7606429319635153`*^9, 
   3.760642946184031*^9}, {3.760643099797296*^9, 3.760643188108944*^9}, {
   3.760643226753291*^9, 3.760643238862667*^9}, {3.760643343234527*^9, 
   3.760643361069058*^9}, {3.76064349367705*^9, 3.760643534433504*^9}, {
   3.760643608463779*^9, 3.760643634434759*^9}, {3.760643916989945*^9, 
   3.76064407491961*^9}, {3.760644140809655*^9, 3.760644205629078*^9}, 
   3.760644359185997*^9, {3.760644449894362*^9, 3.760644460348439*^9}, {
   3.760645562995447*^9, 3.760645594382709*^9}, {3.7606508200347548`*^9, 
   3.760650820526434*^9}, {3.760652906042602*^9, 3.7606529084093657`*^9}, {
   3.760653281226163*^9, 3.760653329256733*^9}, {3.76065347713719*^9, 
   3.760653478650423*^9}, {3.7606541214186296`*^9, 3.7606541477422867`*^9}, {
   3.7606543218048077`*^9, 3.760654335214827*^9}, {3.7606545959931927`*^9, 
   3.760654596081286*^9}, {3.760654684371387*^9, 3.760654727802203*^9}, {
   3.7606547626111603`*^9, 
   3.7606547686274233`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2f1a741b-ea32-4e68-967b-\
91d6d9eb09ce"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Deliverable: ",
  FontSize->13,
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["Vary the width and location of the ring in Fourier space and \
include a plot like the one from the last section to show that your spatial \
filter works.\n\n1) Discuss what effects you see in the Siemens star image\n\
2) What purpose can this filter serve in image processing?",
  FontSize->13]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.760653317870872*^9, 3.760653379482809*^9}, {
  3.76065343862327*^9, 3.760653498432395*^9}, {3.760654097147524*^9, 
  3.76065411177414*^9}, {3.7606541679107637`*^9, 3.7606541737865868`*^9}, {
  3.7606542990355253`*^9, 3.76065430770083*^9}, {3.7606547747244883`*^9, 
  3.7606547845038*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"3cfb4ac5-17aa-4750-b823-3ba5a4bfed66"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\t",
 StyleBox["2.2.4 Construct and investigate the effects of a phase contrast \
filter\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\tThe previous examples while useful, can be applied in post processing to \
a recorded image. In this example you will construct a phase contrast \
microscope that essentially transfers phase \tinformation in the object, to \
amplitude information in the image. The phase contrast filter will be very \
similar to the low pass filter from 2.2.1 except it will be a phase only \
object imparting \ta phase shift of \[Pi]/2 to only a portion of the wave. In \
order to test your phase contrast microscope, the input to the system should \
be a phase only object. In this case, we will simply convert our Siemens star \
image into a phase, rather than an amplitude object. An example showing how \
this system works is displayed below:\n\t\n   \t\t     ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  GraphicsBox[
   TagBox[RasterBox[CompressedData["
