  "0d91c37c-53ff-42a6-afc4-75d45af2c4e7"],
 "\n",
 StyleBox["Figure Phase Contrast microscope",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": All planes show AMPLITUDE, not phase. Notice that the input object is \
seen to be completely transparent i.e., a phase only object. The spatial \
filter also has unit amplitude. However, the image plane clearly shows a \
sharp image of the input object.\n\t\t\t\t\nNote that in the figure, the \
error is between the amplitudes of the input and object and is simply an \
image of the object owing to the fact that the input amplitude is unity \
everywhere."
}], "Text",
